topicSummary: Carpal tunnel syndrome (CTS) is a collection of symptoms and signs caused by compression of the median nerve in the carpal tunnel at the wrist.

topicHtmlObjects.htmlHeader: Carpal tunnel syndrome: Summary

latestChanges.title: Reviewed
latestChanges.body: A literature search was conducted in July 2016 to identify evidence-based guidelines, UK policy, systematic reviews, and key RCTs published since the last revision of the topic. No major changes to clinical recommendations have been made.
